Package bus

Class GasVehicle

java.lang.Object
bus.Vehicle
bus.GasVehicle
All Implemented Interfaces:
IMileAgeEfficiency, Serializable
public class GasVehicle extends Vehicle
Represents a gasoline vehicle in the vehicles' fleet factory. Inherits the attributes and methods of the superclass Vehicle and also has the attribute fuelConsumed which represents the energy consumed by this GasVehicle.
Version:
2021-12-14
Author:
Lilas Guan
See Also:
Vehicle, Serialized Form

    • getMilesPerEnergyConsumed

      public double getMilesPerEnergyConsumed()
      Description copied from interface: IMileAgeEfficiency
      Gets the mileage efficiency of the Vehicle and this method will be overridden by the subclasses of the abstract class Vehicle.
      Returns:
      A double by dividing the value of tripCounter with the value of the energy consumed which will depend on the subclass of Vehicle, which represents the mileage efficiency.
      See Also:
      getMilesPerEnergyConsumed(), ElectricVehicle.getMilesPerEnergyConsumed()

      public void makeTrip​(int tripCounter, double energyConsumed)
      Description copied from interface: IMileAgeEfficiency
